Facts (layer 2):

`show` (VariableExpression):
  has bound(s) `Describe` `Number` (resolved as `instance (Describe Number)`)
  has type `Number Number Number -> ()` or `Number -> ()`
  is an expression
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `show :: value -> () where (Describe value)`

`show 1 2 3` (ExpressionStatement):
  has type `()`

`show 1 2 3` (CallExpression):
  has type `()`
  is an expression

`1` (NumberExpression):
  has type `Number`
  is an expression

`2` (NumberExpression):
  has type `Number`
  is an expression

`3` (NumberExpression):
  has type `Number`
  is an expression



Feedback:

`show` (conflicting-types)

  `show` isn't a `Number -> ()`.
  
  
  
  -  `show` is a `Number Number Number -> ()`.
